In github new a repo(make by ChaoYu in Nanjing University Of Posts And telescommunication):
	1, In github new a repo.
	2, In local mkdir <repo> ,then cd <repo> and  then git init .
	3, git remote add origin <ssh clone URL>
		(if edit the https: then we can change it by command : git remote set-url origin git@github.com=yuchaochenjie/My.git)
	4, check the link . git remote -v 
			    ssh -T git@github.com
	5, git pull origin master
	6, then we make the connect .  vim ..  git add .. git status..git commit..git pull -u origin master(the first time pull,and later we will use git pull origin master) 
